    },
    {
      "id": "59e6d79cc2950571e59d05526e11f78300f54579",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-11 19:19:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThis patch failed in 2.1 upgrade testing:\n\n 07:05:02:LustreError: 27939:0:(lustre_idl.h:705:ostid_to_fid()) bad MDT0 id, 0x110:1024 ost_idx:0\n\nit looks like it would be the same problem as is fixed for \"lfs getstripe\" by http://review.whamcloud.com/6026, since I suspect this is a swapped FID.  Sequence 0x200000400 truncated to 32 bits is \"oid\" 1024, and oid 0x110 is the actual OID being used as the sequence.\n\nLooks like this patch needs to be combined with http://review.whamcloud.com/6026 and additional fixes to get the interop handling correct.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c0f6b930324e611ff299a6fd8cccd0a3e9a12435",
      "author": {
